So the night started with one of our friends having an irresistible craving for churros after we did some push ups with one of the DC Police on the steps of the Supreme Court (sorry that's all the context you're getting) and the nearest place that had them was Tortilla Coast. We walked on down, ordered our XXL Churros, which to clarify is an XXL amount of churros not a single one the size of your arm as we had hoped. Nonetheless they were tasty. We walked to a DC park my friend ate it and sliced her arm on broken glass. She's a trooper so she put a napkin on it, rubbed some dirt on it and carried on. We went out separate ways and my friend went back to Tortilla Coast to ask for a band-aid. The hostess, sat her down got her an antiseptic wipe, antibacterial spread and a bandage to clean her up. Friend then bought and beer and waited for her ride to go out for the night (a real trooper I told you). Churros were excellent and the service even better, idk who you were hostess on the night of 17OCT20 but you deserve a raise and a congressional medal of honor. If the service is that good and the churros that tasty I gotta imagine so is the rest of the food at that fine establishment. 11/10 would recommend.

I was there last week with my family and a few friends. When i left the restaurant, i realized that i had forgotten my bag which had 'uncut currency' that my kids bought from the Bureau of Engraving and Printing. Since i was already in the Metro, i called the restaurant immediately and informed them of the situation . I was told that they have the bag with them and can collect it later the next week when i visit D.C. again. I picked up my bag and returned home. Now I see that they went through my bag, removed the currency sheets form their respective envelopes, folded it and tried to tear them (probably to be used as regular currency). I called the restaurant and informed the manager. Was not surprised that the first thing he said was that it would not be his staff who did this. He mentioned that they would have directly handed over my bag to him as soon as they found it. I had nothing further to say when a restaurant who prides themselves in serving good food and drinks doesnt even hear a customer complaint, so I ended the call. I guess then the Bureau may have sold me currency in that condition or I managed to unknowingly destroy a gift that my kids bought. I find this highly disgusting and a violation of my privacy as a customer. Is this how a customer or their belongings get treated? I hope the owners look into this and restore a customers faith in them.

A legendarily mediocre Tex-Mex joint that upgraded to a rather outstanding Tex-Mex joint a few years ago.  If you're familiar with Tex-Mex only by way of Taco Bell, you're missing out. That's not meant to be a knock on Taco Bell, but you wouldn't judge all hamburgers by McDonald's, right? This is classic American casual cuisine that deserves to be enjoyed as much as any greasy spoon, soul food, or American Chinese restaurant.  Tortilla Coast has really good Tex-Mex now. Maybe the Texans in your life could disagree, but let this institution have it's deserved moment in the sun. It's convenient for lunch after Hill meetings, so it gets very busy on weekday afternoons. Try visiting for weekend brunch, when it becomes just a sleepy neighborhood dive.  Everything you've heard about the Coast is true... including this review!

It makes me sad to give this place a not-so-great review. I have been a regular to this place for years. it has always been the best restaurant on Capitol Hill, hands down. The staff is great! And it used to be the best chips and salsa you could find anywhere. Recently, in the past few months, it has gone downhill. They have either lost key employees who took their recipes with them or they have switched suppliers or something. The most noticeable change is the salsa. It is no where near as good as it used to be. It never used to be spicy but now it is and also has this strange after-taste. It's definitely a different recipe. The other disappointing thing is the steak used for the fajitas and quesadillas. It's now very fatty and not good quality. They previously had tender, juicy steak full of flavor. It's not poor quality and not very much flavor. Some things are still very yummy but a lot has changed and it's a huge disappointment as we are now looking for a new go-to spot :(

We walked in and the amount of people in this one restaurant was overwhelming, it was around 5 and was loud/packed with young career folk in dress attire just getting off work for drinks. The host immediately greeted us and grabbed us a booster seat for the baby, got us a table by the window and pulled down the blinds so we weren’t being baked. The server came quickly and got our drink orders, even took DD’s sippy to put milk in it for us. I bet he stopped by our table every 5 minutes even though it was insanely crowded. Our drinks were never more than half empty, I didn’t have to ask for an extra plate since the kids shared a kids meal - he just brought one. The host gave me directions to the bathroom (which was like a maze away) and I got lost halfway there. Amazingly he just showed up, said he was worried I’d get lost, and showed me how to get there. I have no idea how a restaurant that is this packed out, with so many people shoulder to shoulder, and low staff, can be this hospitable and attentive to every guest but it was truly impressive. The food was just alright, the portions were decent and my meat was way overcooked like jerky. I got the tuna tacos and meh, it was food and I was hungry but nothing special. The chips were greasy but the salsa however is made in-house and was absolutely delicious. Fortunately for the clearly overwhelmed BOH, the FOH made up for their shortcomings and I only wished my server and host had told us their names so I could brag about their service specifically. With 20 people walking in/out the door it didn’t stop the host from thanking us for coming in and wishing us a good day, as well as apologizing for the noise since we were clearly a traveling family with kids who landed in a busy singles after-work hangout. Absolutely awesome FOH. 4 stars for FOH service, -1 Star for tuna jerky tacos.
